  "texts": [
    "Some images are predicted with high accuracy while others are not.",
    "We assume that the images with poor predictions contain new information that the current model needs to learn, while the images with high accuracy have already been learned.",
    "Based on this assumption, we select the images with poor predictions to be added to the labeled datasets, which helps to strengthen the model's learning ability.",
    "When using a pre-trained model to predict unlabeled images, we can compute the probability of each category to which the samples may belong.",
    "This is done by obtaining the output probabilities from the softmax layer of the model."
